CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, January 21, 1956, pg. A4, reads: "1956 Frontier's Officers - Newly elected officers of the Pittsburgh chapter of the Frontiers of America, met recently and mapped ambitious plans for 1956. On their program are a number of 'firsts' and 'surprises.'  Left to right, front row, J. W. Hicks, first president, and Boyd L. Wilson, president.  Back row, same order, Howard Hairston, treasurer; George Culberson, corresponding secretary, and J. D. Lewis, second vice president. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of officers of Frontiers of America, seated from left: J. W. Hicks, Boyd L. Wilson; standing: Howard Hairston, George Culberson, and J. D. Lewis, in office
